Job SummaryWe are looking for a Solution Architect to engineer technical solutions for web & mobile applications in emerging technologies for Investment-related projects.
Mandatory Skill-set
• Bachelor's Degree in Information Technology, Info Systems, Computer Science or other related disciplines;
• At least 12 years of technical experience in web and mobile application development and management;
• Proficient in React, Redux, Java, HTML, SOAP, CSS, XML and Spring Boot;
• Familiar with Waterfall and Agile models;
• Meticulous and well-versed in systems limitations and solutioning capabilities;
• Strong analytical, creative and problem solving skills;
• Strong stakeholder engagement skills to manage internal and external stakeholders;
• Strong written and verbal communication skills to interact with business and technical teams;
Desired Skill-set
• PMP-certified;
• TOGAF certified;
• Certified ScrumMaster;
• Experience in financial services industry.
Responsibilities
• Responsible for... developing and integrating the organizations information systems;
• Asses the existing systems architecture and recommend solutions to improve it;
• Lead the development team to deliver application projects and other major initiatives;
• Work with cross-systems teams to integrate the systems for better efficiency and effectiveness;
• Define, maintain and comply application design standards to the systems Architecture framework & Enterprise Architecture framework;
• Provide technical leadership on emerging technologies adoption and identify potential opportunities and benefits for implementation;
• Assist with solving technical problems when they arise along with managing production support to ensure incident management within SLA;
• Address technical concerns, ideas and suggestions and groom the development teams to build their capabilities.
Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE's website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

